# Core Structure (Backend)

Define and follow the project package structure:

- **controller** – REST controllers and `@RestControllerAdvice` (e.g. `controller/advice/`)
- **service** – business logic, `@Service`
- **repository** – data access, Spring Data `@Repository` or custom
- **entity** – JPA entities, domain models
- **dto/request**, **dto/response** – request/response DTOs (prefer records)
- **exception** – custom exceptions (e.g. `exception/base/`, `exception/user/`)
- **mapper** – entity ↔ DTO mapping
- **configuration** – `@Configuration` beans
- **security** – security config, JWT, CORS
- **utils** – stateless utilities

Place new classes in the appropriate package. Keep controllers thin; put business logic in services.
